column2: Has rained for 6 days- stormed last night- cloudy day.
Air temp 82- slight wind- partly cloudy- 2 loons with babies- eagle out- 2 otters playing
Cold nights- rain storm 4 days prior to reading- loons still on lake
Hot- heavy rain storm yesterday- calm.
Overcast- slight wind- sent card to 1st secchi dip-in.
Water color in between green + brown.  Ice fell in 4/20/95.  Slight wind 45 degrees F.  Snowed all week.
Warm- 85 degrees- no wind- some blooms on top of water.
Hot 90 degrees weather- more weeds than last year.
Lake smells like it's turning over- warm.
Cold water- lake turning over- fall weather conditions- windy.
Cool nights 50 degrees- warm days- lots of rain.  Lake level: very high
Cool nights- warm days- sunny- 80 degrees- some algae in water.
2 days ago had 1st snowfall. Today very warm- 65 degrees- slight wind. Saw loon on lake still.
Ice off 4-21-97- windy- 1 set of loons returned- saw 2 otters on lake.
Warm- slight wind- 80 degrees.  Lake level: very high
Lake turned over last week.  This week rained for 4 days.
Windy- 1/2 inch of rain last night- hot- humid weather last week.
Partly cloudy.  Heavy rains last night.  Lake level: very high
Lots of rain yesterday- warm with slight breeze- beautiful day
Calm light snow flurries.  2 loons swimming flocks of ducks in water.
Saw mom + baby loon.  Lot of algae clouds in water.
2 loons- overcast- slight wind- lake very low.
Windy- loons still on nest- lake is very low.
Very windy - lots of rain this past week 7 very warm temps until today - Loons hanging around nest - lake very murky - Lake level still low.
Lake level extremely low.  Need rain.  Level down approx. 2 feet.
Lake level very low - No rain in several weeks
Loons off nest + egg is gone have not seen a baby may have been destroyed by a preditor!!!!Lots of fishermen on lake for holiday!!!
level still very low - extreme algae bloom
Lake level cont. to drop.  Lowest I have seen it in 18 years - boat travel getting very tricky dodging stumps and rocks!!!
Lake level lowest its been in 25 years according to oldtime lake residents - hard to maneuver boat safely - very heavy algae bloom last several weeks.
Cloudy- North Wind 10 mph- no boats on lake- no loon sighting.
Clear day- breezy day with small waves. Single loon out swimming- very low boat traffic
Partly sunny with a mild breeze.  No Boats- numerous geese out swimming- 1 loon out swimming/diving- Musk rat swimming- 1 kayaker fishing - many people out swimming and 1 snorkeler.
Mostly Sunny- mild wind- low boat traffic.  Very nice day
No Boats- Sunny- Calm- No Breeze- Fog/mist on lake- Saw ducks and geese. Saw 2 loons the night before.
Calm- clear blue sky- no boats
Partly Cloudy- breezy- no boats- quit- no Loons sighted- many ducks and some geese
Mostly cloudy and breezy.  It has been dry for about a week.  Water down a couple inches.  Two loons out- ducks- geese- numerous turtles and fish activity seems to be increasing.
Beautiful day- clear skies- no wind- lake was calm- no boats.
Clear hazy day. Slight breeze but clam at the test site. No others boaters. Record heat almost 90 degrees in September.
Windy day- hazy- spotted loons- ducks- turtles.  However- reported winter fish kill- fishing no activity or fish spotted.
Breezy and hazy  - Not catching or seeing any fish.  Seeing loons- turtles- ducks- geese
Clumps of what may be blue/green algae. Bladderwort present.

Beautiful weather - sunny- clear- slight breeze.  Saw loons- ducks- and turtles.  No other boats out.  Others on the lake report a few northern.  Our neighbor stated he caught a 9 in perch.  This was the first pan fish that I heard anyone caught all year.  We did see a couple pockets of small fish swirl at the top as our pontoon approach them.

First ice off reading.  Collected water sample for PHOSPHORUS and sent to lab and recorded temperature readings.  Reports from lake owners - stated no fish kill- none floating or on shore this year.  Great News.  Water is still high but to the eye looks clearer.  Seccki disk readings better up to 7 feet from 5 feet last year.
Sunny- winding- very nice day.  Water looked great and was high - a lot of docks under water.  Saw a turtle- 3 loons- numerous ducks and eagles soaring over head.
Excellent day- clear- slight wind- loons out- ducks- turtles.  Catch a small northern.  No reports of any other fish being caught.
Breezy day and sunny. Fishing reports from other lake owners were - No fish.  Saw Loons- turtles- beaver and ducks.  1 other boater.

column1: Collected June water sample and sent to state lab.  Also recorded water temperature.

column2: Blue Sky- Sunny- and calm.  Saw two sets of loons on each side of the lake.  One set had a baby loon and was doing well.  Reports from long time residents on lake state that this was the first baby loon that survived since the 1990's.

column1: Did the July water sample and sent to state lab.  Also did Secchi and temperature readings..

column2: windy- sunny and cool.  Saw loons with baby.  Baby is getting big.  Caught some small pan fish and very small bass.
